Azure Resource Locks prevent accidental deletion or modification of critical resources. There are two types:

* CanNotDelete (Delete lock)
* ReadOnly lock

For example, applying a delete lock on a production database ensures that no one can accidentally remove it.

A real-life use case is protecting production environments. A company can apply locks on critical resources such as databases and virtual machines.

Another example is preventing configuration changes in sensitive systems like healthcare or financial platforms.

Locks act as an additional layer of protection beyond RBAC.
